frameDefinitions: A New filler occupies a Role or serves a Function after the Old filler ceases to occupy the position.
These words refer to separating a Whole into Parts, or separating one part from another.
An Agent or Entity becomes sufficient enough to meet a Standard.
A Figure is (stably) located with respect to a Ground in terms of how the distance between them compares to some general or contextually relevant scale.
A State_of_affairs is evaluated as good (or bad), against a background assumption that previously, the State_of_affairs was thought to be unlikely to occur.
A Whole separates into Parts, or one part of a whole, called Part_1, becomes separate from the remaining portion, Part_2.
frameExamples: I <t>divided</t> the class into groups in alphabetical order .
This paper does not <t>meet</t> the requirements for graduation.
This small channel meanders through marsh and wetland, <t>splitting</t> into several smaller channels that empty into Lake St. Clair.
